  summarize(ACC = mean(ACC))

## 2 both      2       0.696
## 3 front     1       0.881
## 4 front     2       0.678
## 5 side      1       0.856
## 6 side      2       0.680
ppt_acc_S1 <- filter(angleLearn, Session == 1) %>% group_by(Subject) %>% 
     summarize(ACC = mean(ACC))
ppt_acc_S2 <- filter(angleLearn, Session == 2) %>% group_by(Subject) %>% 
     summarize(ACC = mean(ACC))

Looks like no significant differences in accuracy across conditions at either session. Side is worst at Session 1, Front is worst as Session 2. Overall accuacy drops ~17-20% between S1 and S2.

Plot Accuracy data:

angleLearn %>% group_by(Session, Condition) %>% 
  summarize(Error = mean(Error)) %>% 
  ggplot + geom_line(aes(x = Session, y = Error, group = Condition, 
                         colour = Condition)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0,0.35)) +
  geom_dl(aes(x = Session, y = Error, label = Condition), method = list(dl.combine("last.points"), cex = 0.8)) + 
  theme_minimal(base_size = 16) +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  ggtitle('ErrorRate by Session & Condition')

angleLearn %>% group_by(Session, Condition) %>% 
  summarize(Error = mean(Error)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = factor(Session, level = c("1", "2")),
             y = Error, fill = Condition)) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', position = position_dodge()) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 0.35)) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 18) +
  ggtitle('Error Rate by Session and Condition') + xlab('Condition')

}
